    NAME
        EPC_FLUSH       (LOCK)

    FUNCTION
        Flush current sample from memory. This is the same as finding the
        current sample with EPC_GETSAMPLE and freeing the memory where it's
        waveform is stored:
        FreeMem (sample->waveform, sample->length);
        sample->length = 0;

    INPUTS
        epm_Command =   EPC_FLUSH
        epm_Data    =   NULL

    RESULT
        epm_Error will equal EPCERR_NOERR if sucessful or an error defined in
        extproc.h.

    SEE ALSO


